WEBVTT

00:01.506 --> 00:04.772
You are listening to a message from First Baptist Church, Wichita Falls.

00:05.293 --> 00:14.329
For more information about First Baptist, click the link in the show notes or go to FBCWN.org.

00:14.349 --> 00:18.637
Today's message comes from Senior Pastor, Dr. Bob McCartney.

00:18.657 --> 00:24.708
Let's take our Bibles this morning and open them to 2 Corinthians, chapter 12, verse 7.

00:25.289 --> 00:25.970
Welcome.

00:27.010 --> 00:32.436
Welcome to those of you in 11 o'clockies at Shepherd campus, at West campus.

00:32.896 --> 00:39.003
Glad that you're here this morning for the second message in a series we're calling Into the Valley.

00:40.084 --> 00:52.658
Not all of life is going to be lived on a high, not all of life is going to be lived on the mountaintop, and there are going to be moments when we're going to descend into the valley, and today we're going to talk about descending into a valley

00:52.834 --> 00:55.998
that becomes very, very real for a lot of people.

00:56.098 --> 01:01.446
And that is the valley of chronic illness and pain.

01:02.727 --> 01:06.913
Today we're gonna talk about what happens when your miracle doesn't come.

01:07.814 --> 01:11.920
And by that I mean maybe your physical miracle for healing.

01:12.360 --> 01:16.105
The good news is Americans are living longer.

01:16.546 --> 01:18.108
Our lifespans are increasing.

01:18.148 --> 01:22.514
There was kind of a blip or a small dip in the COVID pandemic.

01:22.626 --> 01:25.610
But the arrow actually keeps going up into the right.

01:25.711 --> 01:27.153
Americans are living longer.

01:27.593 --> 01:36.206
The downside of that or the dark side is that Americans are living longer, but they're living with sometimes chronic illness and pain.

01:36.226 --> 01:48.785
76%, that's three out of four of adults over the age of 40 live with some sort of chronic illness or some sort of chronic pain.

01:49.306 --> 01:52.210
Now, many of them can be managed with

01:52.290 --> 01:57.717
medication or with therapy, and we are thankful for the advances of medical science.

01:58.337 --> 02:14.557
But some people live with excruciating pain, and about 24%, one out of every four say that the pain or the problem that they have physically keeps them from living the lifestyle that they would like to live.

02:14.957 --> 02:17.480
So this is a very, very real issue.

02:18.041 --> 02:22.066
If you live long enough, something's gonna hurt.

02:23.042 --> 02:28.747
I was down at the Expo for the Hotter in Hell this year, and there was this guy who walked in.

02:28.787 --> 02:30.749
He looked like he's about 75 years old.

02:30.769 --> 02:31.770
He's going to ride the ride.

02:31.810 --> 02:34.012
He walks in on his t-shirt.

02:34.253 --> 02:38.096
It had a very simple message, and it said, everything hurts.

02:39.217 --> 02:45.944
I mean, you get to that point where you just, you're going to have to manage it or live with it or surrender to it.

02:46.704 --> 02:52.530
But this morning, we're going to talk about this valley that many of us are going to walk through.

02:52.802 --> 02:55.986
and it is the valley of chronic illness.

02:57.268 --> 02:59.130
For some people, it is cancer.

02:59.851 --> 03:03.717
For others, there's heart disease or kidney disease.

03:04.358 --> 03:13.069
For some people, there are autoimmune disorders that become excruciatingly painful and affect their lives in deep ways.

03:13.149 --> 03:18.116
There's rheumatoid arthritis and a lot of problems that begin to creep up on people.

03:18.476 --> 03:22.642
Some early onset, sometimes it happens later in life,

03:23.010 --> 03:24.532
But there are other issues too.

03:24.552 --> 03:31.462
A lot of times when we think about these issues, we think, well, well, he's really preaching this sermon today, like to the old people, because they're the ones that get this stuff, right?

03:32.323 --> 03:35.748
Well, cancer affects almost every generation.

03:35.968 --> 03:39.033
It's not unheard of, at least we have to be honest and say that.

03:39.694 --> 03:46.503
But also, there are other issues that are very real for younger people, like the issue of infertility.

03:47.805 --> 03:51.250
It's very, very painful, not only physically, but emotionally.

03:51.746 --> 04:02.277
when you want a child and you come to church and man, everybody celebrated the new babies that people were given and you want one really bad.

04:02.837 --> 04:04.879
And my wife and I walk through that valley.

04:06.040 --> 04:10.285
And so by the way, I do have, I make a covenant with couples.

04:11.125 --> 04:18.233
And that is that if you struggle with infertility, if you will send me an email, I will add you to my personal prayer list.

04:18.293 --> 04:19.634
I'm gonna be on the church prayer list.

04:20.034 --> 04:37.939
I will put you on my personal prayer list and I will pray for you every day until you send me the message that God has given you a baby or you've decided that maybe that's not God's will, but I will pray for you every day personally because that's kind of a burden that I have for people I understand that.

04:37.959 --> 04:44.067
But let me say this, it also happens in younger people's lives through perhaps accidents or injuries.

04:45.189 --> 04:49.074
A young man wants to play Major League Baseball and

04:49.506 --> 04:59.458
All of a sudden something goes wrong with a shoulder or with tendons and the doctors say, you know, we can patch you up, but you're never gonna play the sport that you love again.

04:59.539 --> 05:07.889
So these are very real issues, not just for older people, but they can be very real for all of us.

05:07.969 --> 05:13.116
And so we're gonna talk about this today because there is this real tension of three issues.

05:14.297 --> 05:18.322
If you love the Bible, if you love God, there are some things you believe

05:18.562 --> 05:21.626
But sometimes they're like a tug of war on one another.

05:22.908 --> 05:25.272
One is we believe that God is Almighty.

05:25.873 --> 05:27.074
The Bible teaches that.

05:27.235 --> 05:30.540
We affirm that God can do anything.

05:31.501 --> 05:33.344
He can heal, he can restore.

05:33.644 --> 05:36.188
There is nothing that is too difficult for God.

05:36.528 --> 05:37.490
God is Almighty.

05:38.551 --> 05:41.736
We affirm that God is good.

05:41.876 --> 05:43.979
We sing about that.

05:44.821 --> 05:45.842
We believe in the

05:45.922 --> 05:53.393
goodness of God, that his thoughts and his actions toward us are motivated out of a heart that is good.

05:53.433 --> 05:58.180
And then there's that third reality.

05:58.200 --> 06:02.807
Horrible, awful things happen.

06:05.370 --> 06:07.293
And those things pull at one another.

06:08.355 --> 06:13.362
If God is good and God is Almighty, one of these awful things happen

06:14.946 --> 06:16.788
And why do they happen to me?

06:17.889 --> 06:19.170
That's really where it comes down.

06:20.091 --> 06:31.703
So this morning we're going to explore this from a passage of scripture in which one of God's choice servants experiences a chronic issue of illness and pain.

06:33.004 --> 06:39.190
And he tells us in the beginning part of this chapter that 14, for 14 years this has been going on.

06:40.151 --> 06:42.994
This isn't a little cold that he had for a while.

06:43.266 --> 06:46.371
This is something that's been going on for 14 years, 14 years earlier.

06:47.413 --> 06:49.396
God gave him a revelation.

06:50.237 --> 06:50.998
His name is Paul.

06:52.000 --> 06:55.365
And God, he says he was taken up into the third heaven.

06:56.267 --> 07:00.213
And what that means is that in the Greek mindset, there are three levels of heaven.

07:00.253 --> 07:03.659
The first heaven is like the sky and the clouds.

07:04.039 --> 07:06.824
The second heaven is the stars and the sun, the moon, the planets.

07:07.705 --> 07:10.770
But the third heaven is like where God dwells.

07:11.426 --> 07:13.969
And so Paul says, I was caught up into the third heaven.

07:15.190 --> 07:18.153
I saw things that I can't explain to you.

07:18.273 --> 07:26.000
I experienced the presence of God in a real manifest way, not just something that was feeling.

07:26.020 --> 07:27.462
He said it was tangible.

07:28.703 --> 07:34.729
And because of that, he says something incredibly consequential happened in his life.

07:34.789 --> 07:39.634
Listen to what he says in verse seven of 2 Corinthians 12.

07:40.738 --> 08:00.166
Because of the extraordinary greatness of the revelations, for this reason, to keep me from exalting myself, there was given to me a thorn in the flesh, a messenger of Satan to torment me, to keep me from exalting myself.

08:01.107 --> 08:08.978
Concerning this, I pleaded with the Lord three times that it might leave me.

08:09.922 --> 08:14.647
And he has said to me, my grace is sufficient for you.

08:15.447 --> 08:17.990
For power is perfected in weakness.

08:18.791 --> 08:29.020
Most gladly therefore, I will rather boast about my weaknesses so that the power of Christ may dwell in me.

08:29.060 --> 08:39.090
Therefore I delight in weaknesses, in insults, in distresses, in persecutions, in difficulties,

08:39.170 --> 08:47.945
in behalf of Christ for when I am weak, then I am strong."

08:47.965 --> 09:05.074
Let's talk about this fact of life, of how you manage it, how do you cope, how do you move forward in your faith, insanity, when your miracle doesn't come.

09:06.306 --> 09:10.773
Well, Paul talks about a thorn in the flesh here, so we're going to sort of center on that.

09:11.774 --> 09:13.897
And I want to give you three thoughts from this passage.

09:13.957 --> 09:18.584
First of all, we need to learn there is a reason for the thorn.

09:19.846 --> 09:24.593
We need to learn there are reasons that these thorns show up in our life.

09:24.673 --> 09:25.615
It is not random.

09:26.476 --> 09:29.540
Paul says there was given to me a thorn in the flesh.

09:29.580 --> 09:36.050
Now, when you think thorn, you're thinking about that little sharp pointy

09:36.322 --> 09:42.651
part of a rose that kind of pricks your finger if you pick up a rose the wrong way and you're negligent in that.

09:42.731 --> 09:50.241
It might even draw just a little bit of blood, but that is not what that word means in the language of the New Testament.

09:50.441 --> 09:54.587
In the Greek New Testament, that word doesn't mean splinter.

09:55.688 --> 09:57.010
It means a stake.

09:57.922 --> 10:03.471
This is something that would have caused excruciating pain in Paul's life.

10:03.831 --> 10:05.995
It was not some minor nuisance.

10:06.376 --> 10:10.142
It was an absolutely debilitating condition.

10:11.003 --> 10:17.734
Now Bible scholars have debated what this was for centuries.

10:17.774 --> 10:22.962
You can read 10 commentaries and get 11 opinions about what this thing was, okay?

10:23.234 --> 10:27.542
Some people say it was the consequences, the lingering consequences of malaria.

10:27.582 --> 10:35.596
Once you get malaria, you have problems with it forever and there was no vaccination, there was no medication for malaria back then.

10:36.277 --> 10:38.401
Other people say it was Paul's eyesight.

10:38.421 --> 10:43.570
You think about somebody like Paul who loved to read, who loved to study, who loved to write.

10:44.051 --> 10:47.858
Failing eyesight could be a real debilitating problem.

10:48.226 --> 10:50.590
Other people say a variety of other things.

10:50.970 --> 10:55.397
And so I've studied it real hard this week and I've dug in and I've come to an answer.

10:56.038 --> 10:58.001
We don't know.

11:00.124 --> 11:00.504
We don't know.

11:02.027 --> 11:03.849
But I do believe a couple of things about it.

11:03.889 --> 11:06.233
First of all, it's a thorn, it's a stake.

11:07.074 --> 11:08.035
So it's very painful.

11:08.376 --> 11:09.257
It's in the flesh.

11:09.878 --> 11:14.084
It was some sort of physical condition that he had.

11:15.026 --> 11:17.810
Now, I believe personally,

11:18.178 --> 11:21.503
that the language here is purposefully vague.

11:22.765 --> 11:37.246
Because if Paul would have said, you know, God gave me this messenger from Satan, this, this eyesight problem, then every other problem that we have, we would say, well, would the Paul don't know how I feel.

11:37.266 --> 11:44.717
But with it being sort of purposefully vague, then all of our issues can fit into the category.

11:45.057 --> 11:45.618
And I think

11:45.698 --> 11:48.843
Sometimes God gives us very specific instructions in the Bible.

11:49.284 --> 11:56.655
Sometimes they're a little bit more broad in order for us for our issue, whatever it might be to be included in the bunch.

11:57.617 --> 12:00.481
Also look carefully at the source of this problem.

12:01.643 --> 12:03.706
He says, there was given to me.

12:03.766 --> 12:06.631
That's an important word.

12:07.372 --> 12:11.218
And he calls it a messenger of Satan to torment me.

12:13.186 --> 12:23.304
When I've read this passage over and over in the past, and I've preached it before, I have talked about how Satan is the source of this pain, and Paul does call it a messenger of Satan.

12:23.845 --> 12:29.514
But there's something really interesting in this that, look, I want you to understand something.

12:29.635 --> 12:33.842
I learn something every week, and I probably learn more than I'm able to share with you in the sermon.

12:34.562 --> 12:40.270
But that word given is incredibly important and I had never really dug in and dissected this before.

12:40.731 --> 12:44.576
The word given is the word edote in the language of the New Testament.

12:45.237 --> 12:52.708
And when it is used in literature, it is always referring to a divine gift.

12:53.469 --> 12:55.592
It's a gift from God.

12:56.033 --> 12:59.858
And so when he says it was given to me, then

13:00.034 --> 13:01.656
God is the one doing the giving.

13:01.676 --> 13:03.298
He said, but he calls it a messenger of Satan.

13:03.318 --> 13:04.600
Well, how is that possible?

13:05.061 --> 13:05.642
Let me help you.

13:06.523 --> 13:09.066
There's a story in the Old Testament, a story of a man named Job.

13:09.106 --> 13:11.930
And Job lost everything.

13:12.671 --> 13:13.853
He lost his health.

13:13.933 --> 13:14.854
He lost his wealth.

13:14.874 --> 13:15.856
He lost his family.

13:16.817 --> 13:24.948
And every time he lost, but before he lost something, every time Satan had to go ask God for permission to afflict Job.

13:26.090 --> 13:27.111
Here's what I want you to know.

13:27.351 --> 13:29.394
Satan may strike you.

13:29.698 --> 13:32.241
but God always supervises.

13:33.642 --> 13:35.064
Satan is not equal with God.

13:35.865 --> 13:40.570
Satan is under God and God is the one who is in control.

13:40.950 --> 13:42.832
But here's the uncomfortable part of that.

13:43.934 --> 13:46.436
God does allow it.

13:47.978 --> 13:52.003
And that is really uncomfortable and it's hard for us to take.

13:53.064 --> 13:55.566
So what are the reasons for these thorns?

13:55.827 --> 13:57.949
Let me give you three real quick.

13:57.969 --> 13:58.770
First of all,

13:58.850 --> 14:05.560
The first reason that we have illness and pain and physical problems is because we live in a broken world.

14:07.103 --> 14:10.288
Adam and Eve were placed in the Garden of Eden, which was perfect.

14:11.490 --> 14:19.482
And in Genesis chapter one and Genesis chapter two, what we get is this wonderful story of a place of perfection.

14:20.684 --> 14:23.929
There was no pain in the Garden of Eden.

14:24.931 --> 14:26.994
There were no problems in the Garden of Eden.

14:27.650 --> 14:30.775
There was no physical illness in the Garden of Eden.

14:31.256 --> 14:34.201
I mean, they could go smell the flowers and not get allergies.

14:34.562 --> 14:36.946
It was absolutely wonderful.

14:38.128 --> 14:45.601
But when sin enters the picture, here's what the Bible says, that with sin, you get a consequence.

14:45.841 --> 14:47.604
And that consequence is death.

14:49.127 --> 14:53.394
Physical death comes into the world as a result of the fallen sin.

14:54.210 --> 15:10.002
So everything that ultimately leads us to physical death, the fact that our bodies begin to wear out as we age, the fact that when you turned your ankle and you were 17, two days later, you were back.

15:10.370 --> 15:23.088
Back on the playing field when you turn your ankle and you were 35 years old in a you kind of limped around for a week And then you got back into the action when you turn your ankle and you're 61 a month later.

15:23.129 --> 15:35.186
You're going maybe I ought to go to the doctor about this or maybe I did something bad I mean stuff just doesn't heal as fast as it used to that's just that's a fact and Not only that but these chronic conditions

15:35.394 --> 15:46.790
begin to creep in whether they are inherited from our families because the genes just don't work exactly right or whether it is something that we do to ourselves through some injury.

15:47.330 --> 15:51.416
Illness and pain is a part of the fall in sin.

15:51.857 --> 15:55.341
Part of the reason that you suffer may not be personal disobedience.

15:55.722 --> 15:58.446
It may not be that you have done anything wrong.

15:58.946 --> 16:02.251
It may well be that it's just a part of living in this world.

16:03.272 --> 16:04.434
But there is a second reason.

16:05.538 --> 16:09.242
And the second reason you need to understand is spiritual.

16:10.263 --> 16:16.290
And it is because sometimes we experience pain because it is the disciplining hand of God.

16:17.771 --> 16:22.476
Now that's not a joyful thought, but it's true.

16:23.738 --> 16:31.506
In Hebrews chapter 12, the writer of Hebrews said, furthermore, we had earthly fathers to discipline us.

16:32.162 --> 16:43.761
And we respected them, shall we not much rather be subject to the father of spirits and live, for they disciplined us for a short time as it seemed best to them.

16:44.722 --> 16:52.375
But he disciplines us for our good so that we may share in his holiness.

16:53.677 --> 16:59.506
The writer of Hebrews says that the father disciplines

16:59.970 --> 17:02.754
everyone that he accepts as his child.

17:03.775 --> 17:07.520
When you came into the family of God, you got a good, good father.

17:08.942 --> 17:20.657
And a good father is not just a live it up, party it up, Disneyland dad, no discipline.

17:20.677 --> 17:23.301
No, a good father disciplines his children.

17:24.062 --> 17:25.283
And we have a good father.

17:26.284 --> 17:27.506
And so there are moments

17:28.002 --> 17:32.969
that he disciplines us for our good, and sometimes that means physical affliction.

17:34.030 --> 17:38.396
There is a third reason, and that's the reason that Paul gives us.

17:38.416 --> 17:39.257
It's a protection.

17:40.399 --> 17:42.201
Sometimes pain is a protection.

17:42.582 --> 17:50.973
Paul says the reason, in verse seven he says, for this reason, to keep me from exalting myself.

17:50.993 --> 17:54.397
It was a protection against sin in Paul's life.

17:55.739 --> 17:57.842
Sometimes God allows

17:58.338 --> 18:09.509
things to come into our lives that are personally painful because what he is doing is protecting us because in our flesh we would go off the rails.

18:10.810 --> 18:13.113
What God understood from Paul was this.

18:13.673 --> 18:21.381
He gave Paul this great privilege of this incredible revelation that Paul saw things that nobody else had ever seen before.

18:21.661 --> 18:23.262
Paul experienced things.

18:23.543 --> 18:25.445
Paul knew the presence of God in a real way.

18:25.485 --> 18:26.866
He was face to face.

18:26.978 --> 18:29.881
in the presence of God in this vision.

18:29.901 --> 18:35.087
And because of that, Paul would have had a tendency to grow prideful.

18:36.008 --> 18:36.869
Pride is a sin.

18:37.550 --> 18:38.090
It really is.

18:39.392 --> 18:49.523
And there are other sins that God may be protecting you from when he allows something to come into your life that is personally painful.

18:50.664 --> 18:55.890
Eric, I'm Eric Wayne Hymer, was four years old.

18:56.450 --> 19:01.077
when he was diagnosed with a degenerative eye disease.

19:01.999 --> 19:06.205
Over the next decade, his vision got progressively worse.

19:06.465 --> 19:17.222
At first, he could see fine then, he couldn't see at night, and then his peripheral vision began to narrow, and eventually, the lights went out.

19:18.564 --> 19:22.450
By the age of 13, he was completely blind.

19:24.450 --> 19:29.615
But he decided that he would not allow that physical condition to stop him.

19:30.476 --> 19:38.263
And so in 2003, he became the first blind person to ever climb Mount Everest.

19:39.264 --> 19:40.005
It's pretty impressive.

19:41.306 --> 19:47.692
Eric said, quote, I can't control blindness, but I can control how I respond.

19:48.513 --> 19:49.874
Pain doesn't make you weaker.

19:50.595 --> 19:53.938
It becomes the training ground for strength.

19:55.266 --> 20:01.994
You can't control what happens to you, but you can control your response to what happens to you.

20:02.595 --> 20:05.178
So learn that there are reasons for the thorns.

20:06.139 --> 20:11.566
Second, listen for the Lord in the thorns.

20:12.868 --> 20:14.930
Listen very carefully.

20:15.731 --> 20:24.722
You see, our response to pain is to cry out, but the answer is found in listening.

20:25.922 --> 20:28.746
Paul says in verse eight, concerning this.

20:29.767 --> 20:35.615
I pleaded with the Lord three times that it might leave me.

20:36.937 --> 20:37.498
Three times.

20:38.078 --> 20:44.267
Now when you hear that, this isn't like Paul says, like three nights in a row.

20:45.228 --> 20:47.131
I prayed, now I lay me down to sleep.

20:48.212 --> 20:50.715
Lord, please take this pain away in Jesus' name, amen.

20:51.496 --> 20:52.698
No, that's not it.

20:53.800 --> 20:55.602
It was three

20:55.810 --> 21:03.418
seasons, extended seasons of intense fervent prayer.

21:04.299 --> 21:06.782
He uses the word I pleaded.

21:06.842 --> 21:11.627
That is a word in the New Testament for a beggar asking for bread.

21:12.568 --> 21:14.971
He begged God.

21:15.771 --> 21:20.456
God, please take this pain away.

21:21.858 --> 21:25.682
Some of you have begged God.

21:27.074 --> 21:32.522
You have been on your knees and there have been prayers that have been prayed through bitter tears.

21:33.444 --> 21:35.527
And you have pleaded with God.

21:35.547 --> 21:40.054
And you've said, God, please take this pain away.

21:41.976 --> 21:44.761
And you received the same thing the Apostle Paul received.

21:46.523 --> 21:49.027
A gentle, but firm.

21:50.449 --> 21:50.629
No.

21:52.232 --> 21:53.213
And that's hard to take.

21:54.475 --> 21:56.338
It's really hard.

21:56.514 --> 21:56.915
to take.

21:58.236 --> 22:07.008
I say that to you to encourage you though, that one of God's choice servants, the Apostle Paul, I mean like he's one of the heroes of the faith in the New Testament.

22:08.771 --> 22:11.675
He didn't get the answer that he wanted to his prayer.

22:13.076 --> 22:18.404
Can I tell you that there was even a moment when Jesus received a gentle but firm no from the Father?

22:19.625 --> 22:20.066
It happened.

22:21.127 --> 22:23.270
It happened in the Garden of Gethsemane.

22:23.290 --> 22:26.034
In the Garden of Gethsemane, Jesus was praying.

22:26.722 --> 22:33.293
And he prayed, Father, if you are willing, remove this cup from me, yet not my will, but yours be done.

22:33.854 --> 22:36.058
Father, could you please remove this cup?

22:36.078 --> 22:37.821
He knows the cross is in front of him.

22:38.782 --> 22:41.006
And the Father responds, no.

22:41.727 --> 22:44.071
There's no other way.

22:47.156 --> 22:53.106
You see, when God says no, it's always because he has a better yes.

22:54.658 --> 23:03.750
When he would not remove the cup of suffering and the cup that Jesus had to drink on the cross, when he would not remove that from him, it's because he had a better yes.

23:03.830 --> 23:07.195
And that better yes was a gospel that would save you and me.

23:09.398 --> 23:15.166
See, when God says no, he always has a better yes.

23:16.768 --> 23:21.234
Paul says, I asked God, I begged God, I pleaded with God,

23:22.658 --> 23:35.514
in verse nine, and he has said to me, that expression he has said looks like it's past tense in the English translation.

23:36.375 --> 23:40.140
The Greek language has a lot of tenses, more than past, present, future.

23:40.861 --> 23:42.944
This is in what is called the perfect tense.

23:43.785 --> 23:47.129
In other words, it means he said once and for all.

23:48.050 --> 23:51.314
God says, I am settling this issue, the answer

23:51.522 --> 23:55.128
is a firm and final no.

23:56.570 --> 24:01.017
I'm going to tell you, when God says no, it's hard.

24:02.659 --> 24:03.140
It's hard.

24:05.063 --> 24:11.653
There are moments when you question the power of God and you question the goodness of God.

24:13.215 --> 24:17.682
And even when you don't get a no, maybe what's worse than no is just the silence.

24:20.066 --> 24:21.628
Some of you in this room have felt that too.

24:22.950 --> 24:24.031
But I want to say this to you.

24:25.433 --> 24:29.238
The silence of God is not the absence of God.

24:31.881 --> 24:35.526
Though God may be silent, he is not absent.

24:37.148 --> 24:48.402
Because what he may be doing is drawing you very, very close to him so that you can experience a level of his love and provision that you had not known before.

24:49.602 --> 24:52.626
Tim Keller was a prolific author.

24:52.686 --> 24:54.448
I think he wrote like over 30 books.

24:56.751 --> 25:05.922
One of the most brilliant minds of our generation when it came to the things of God, planted a church from nothing in New York City.

25:06.743 --> 25:13.031
And Redeemer became a lighthouse for the gospel in that pagan city.

25:14.513 --> 25:18.738
But Tim Keller was diagnosed with pancreatic cancer.

25:19.714 --> 25:26.523
And I gotta be honest with you, I'm not one to question the wisdom of Almighty God, but I'm like, God, Tim Keller's doing great things.

25:27.805 --> 25:31.290
I mean, he's not even a Baptist, he's a Presbyterian, but I mean, we're on the same team.

25:31.850 --> 25:35.315
And as far as I'm concerned, we're on the same team if you're preaching the same gospel.

25:35.936 --> 25:41.844
So I'm like, God, he's doing great things and people are getting saved and wonderful things are happening.

25:41.864 --> 25:46.410
He's bringing glory to your name and the kingdom of God is expanding by what he's doing.

25:46.450 --> 25:49.394
And so why are you,

25:50.018 --> 25:54.124
letting him have this messenger of Satan that is pancreatic cancer.

25:56.187 --> 26:01.696
In the last few days or months of his life, he gave an interview and won the last interviews that he gave.

26:02.858 --> 26:14.896
And he said this, the greatest gift of this illness is that it has brought me closer to the reality of God's love than I ever imagined.

26:17.060 --> 26:18.642
He experienced

26:19.010 --> 26:24.399
a greater measure of the love of God in the midst of personal pain.

26:26.462 --> 26:29.968
Listen for the Lord in the thorns.

26:30.930 --> 26:34.696
Finally, look for the blessings in the thorn.

26:36.899 --> 26:38.682
Look for the blessings in the thorn.

26:40.185 --> 26:45.874
In verse nine, Paul said, and he has said to me, and then he tells us what God told him.

26:47.298 --> 26:55.126
My grace is sufficient for you, for power is perfected in weakness.

26:57.349 --> 27:01.933
The word sufficient means to satisfy.

27:02.074 --> 27:02.995
It means enough.

27:05.177 --> 27:13.906
When we use the word enough, most of the time we use it and we mean this, enough to get by.

27:16.002 --> 27:17.543
That's not what that Greek word means.

27:19.786 --> 27:22.028
It doesn't mean enough to get by.

27:22.568 --> 27:25.451
God doesn't just say, Paul, I'll give you enough to get by.

27:26.812 --> 27:29.455
It means enough to satisfy.

27:30.876 --> 27:34.080
My grace will satisfy you, Paul.

27:35.201 --> 27:39.505
Just surrender to where you are and what is happening.

27:42.027 --> 27:44.850
And I will make my power perfect.

27:45.122 --> 27:46.764
in the middle of your weakness.

27:47.485 --> 27:49.448
Yeah, I've thought about this a lot this week.

27:50.910 --> 27:51.610
And it's amazing.

27:52.872 --> 28:00.182
When somebody is, you know, healthy and strong and they give a testimony for Christ, I mean, it's a great thing.

28:00.282 --> 28:09.213
I love that like when athletes or when someone who has a platform, they give glory to God for what's happening in their life, I think that's wonderful.

28:10.775 --> 28:12.818
But you know, I think even more powerful.

28:14.850 --> 28:19.756
is when someone is weak, and when they have problems.

28:21.619 --> 28:41.985
When someone like Nick Vuyashish, whom we've had here in our church, born with no arms and no legs, when Nick gives glory to God, I mean, I watch Nick and I'm like, my back hurts.

28:42.005 --> 28:42.866
So what?

28:43.522 --> 28:47.548
I have arms and legs and He's giving glory to God and I'm lining.

28:47.588 --> 28:56.202
There is something about that that really is powerful, that God's power is made perfect.

28:56.262 --> 28:57.885
It's perfected in our weakness.

28:59.688 --> 29:08.882
But let me also give you a reason that sometimes God doesn't take pain away because your pain is your platform.

29:11.362 --> 29:13.925
You are, I know you think you're unique.

29:14.046 --> 29:14.466
I know you do.

29:14.566 --> 29:17.751
I think I'm unique, but you aren't.

29:20.494 --> 29:23.038
Somebody had your problem before you got it.

29:24.339 --> 29:29.326
Somebody's gonna have your problem after you have it.

29:29.346 --> 29:30.868
You say, well, Bob, that's not really encouraging.

29:33.372 --> 29:34.393
But here's the point.

29:35.735 --> 29:41.202
God wants you to serve out of your scars.

29:44.514 --> 29:54.847
In 2 Corinthians chapter 1, Paul writes, blessed be the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, the Father of mercies and the God of all comfort.

29:56.228 --> 30:11.688
He comforts us in all our afflictions so that we may be able to comfort those who are in any kind of affliction through the comfort we ourselves receive.

30:11.708 --> 30:13.650
Here's what that means if you didn't follow.

30:15.234 --> 30:30.339
When we have personal pain, when we have chronic issues, when we are walking through life, wanting healing and the miracle doesn't come, but God says, my grace is sufficient and God comforts us in that affliction.

30:30.599 --> 30:37.170
Then what Paul is saying is God gave you that comfort to pass on to someone else.

30:38.242 --> 30:47.732
to minister to them, to serve from the scars, to let your pain be your platform in order to bring glory to God in Jesus Christ.

30:50.675 --> 30:52.757
See, God wants to use you.

30:53.999 --> 30:54.519
He really does.

30:54.579 --> 31:04.850
He wants to use your story because there's someone who is far from him that he loves

31:06.786 --> 31:10.451
And it's not going to be the preacher that reaches them.

31:11.453 --> 31:21.066
It will be someone who shares their affliction, who shares their pain, who knows what it feels like to walk through that problem.

31:24.331 --> 31:30.920
And they say, Jesus helped me through this and he can help you too.

31:32.923 --> 31:35.026
Jesus provided for me through this.

31:35.810 --> 31:44.099
His grace became the grace that satisfies, and that just gets me by, but that satisfies me through this.

31:46.281 --> 31:50.145
For my generation, one of the movie stars that we loved was Michael J.

31:50.185 --> 31:52.508
Fox.

31:52.588 --> 31:57.193
Even some of you who are younger, you've watched the back to the future movies.

31:57.453 --> 31:58.794
They're classics now.

31:59.215 --> 32:02.418
I realize that means that it's old, but they're classics.

32:03.810 --> 32:04.631
When Michael J.

32:04.651 --> 32:14.283
Fox was 29 years old, 29, he was diagnosed with young, onset Parkinson's disease.

32:14.924 --> 32:17.468
It is incredibly rare but not unheard of.

32:18.409 --> 32:29.884
He hid it for a long time because he still wanted to act and then it got to a place where it was taking such a toll on his body that he simply no longer could act.

32:30.905 --> 32:31.826
He said this,

32:32.450 --> 32:34.593
not long ago in an interview now in his sixties.

32:35.955 --> 32:36.816
I'm not gonna lie.

32:38.098 --> 32:39.620
It stinks, heaven, Parkinson's.

32:40.681 --> 32:43.545
But if I could trade it in, I wouldn't.

32:44.967 --> 32:52.577
It has given me a sense of purpose I never had before.

32:52.597 --> 32:56.663
I don't know what your pain point is.

32:58.886 --> 33:01.970
But there is something about coming to the place of saying,

33:02.626 --> 33:06.510
I wouldn't trade it in because it has given me a purpose.

33:06.550 --> 33:21.384
It has given me an avenue to reach others and to serve and to pour out my heart for Jesus so that others will come to know Him and bring great glory to God.

33:24.426 --> 33:27.689
You've been listening to a message from First Baptist Church, Wichita Falls.

33:28.290 --> 33:32.594
For more information about First Baptist, including gathering times and locations,

33:32.802 --> 33:37.267
Click the link in the show notes or go to FBCWF.org.

33:37.287 --> 33:38.514
We'll see you next week.

